00:09:11.090 --> 00:09:12.590
SURMA: Making it
the default, right?

00:09:12.590 --> 00:09:13.160
JAKE: Yeah.

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:15.482
What can we do for accessibility
to achieve the same?

00:09:15.482 --> 00:09:16.190
ROB DODSON: Yeah.

00:09:16.190 --> 00:09:19.940
So it's tough, because
accessibility--

00:09:19.940 --> 00:09:21.950
because the area is really
broad, some of things

00:09:21.950 --> 00:09:24.500
fall into user
experience and design.

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:26.870
So color contrast and
stuff like that, people

00:09:26.870 --> 00:09:29.210
tend to pick that up,
and incorporate it

00:09:29.210 --> 00:09:32.015
into their design process
a little bit better.

00:09:32.015 --> 00:09:33.640
You get into other
areas, though, like,

00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:35.805
screen reader support in
Aria, and a lot of people

00:09:35.805 --> 00:09:37.680
