not my problem, right.

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:39.050
It's sort of out of
sight, out of mind.

00:09:39.050 --> 00:09:40.010
If it's not something
that's directly

00:09:40.010 --> 00:09:41.150
affecting the developer,
they kind of just

00:09:41.150 --> 00:09:42.530
don't care about it.

00:09:42.530 --> 00:09:45.710
So I think what has been really
successful for a lot of teams

00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:49.230
has been doing a more
inclusive design approach,

00:09:49.230 --> 00:09:51.380
so making sure that
you're bringing in people

00:09:51.380 --> 00:09:54.560
who may have disabilities or
impairments into the design

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:56.900
phase-- into the
product testing phase.

00:09:56.900 --> 00:10:00.680
And you know, even also making
sure that you're employing

00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:02.180
those folks on your team, even.

00:10:02.180 --> 00:10:04.555
Engineers on your team might
have disabilities and things

00:10:04.555 --> 00:10:06.096
like that, because
if it doesn't work

00:10:06.096 --> 00:10:07.770
for literally the
engineer on the team,

00:10:07.770 --> 00:10:09.020
it's not going to ship, right.

00:10:09.020 --> 00:10:09.750
